reviews:
It is very nice hotel with a great location next to almost all Paris best attractions with a very good price
The room had every thing like coffe machine boiler and even a microwave and a cooker small dining table/ study desk and an access to outside balcony since our room were located in ground floor
The staff were really helpful and very polite and friendly

Hello,
After Using this hotel for more than 7 trips, the hotel decided to blacklist me. Let me share with you the reason. on my second trip, I ordered a shipment from BartenderWithAttitude which they shipment later than my checkout date; I asked them to keep the shipment till I send some friends to claim it to find out 2 months later that this shipment was delivered and received by a front desk employee named Micheline who no longer works at the hotel. I asked the hotel to contact her and 3 trips later checking on every trip, they never got my shipment back and I got blacklisted; I actually have the document to prove it. when I called to know the reason for the canceled reservations, they told me when blacklisted you for writing a bad review about us on TripAdvisor. Please be aware that you can be punished for complaining for theft which really tell the guests that will consider this hotel.
Good Day to you, dear guests and TripAdvisor Managing Team

Excellent location- walk to Eiffel Tower, Champs-Élysées, Arc de Triumph, nearby cafes. Catherine de Medicis suitewas clean and spacious. We loved the outdoor terrace for coffee and drinks. The staff was so helpful to us. Would love to stay again.

We enjoyed our stay at this hotel. Easy walk to the Champs and Eiffel Tower. Quiet street and we recommend using the laundry service next door and the cafe down the street. We had two rooms and they were spacious by Paris standards. Modern decor with larger than queen beds. Breakfast was delivered to our rooms daily with coffee, juice, yogurt, and pastries. We had a very pleasant experience and would recommend to anyone looking for a reasonably priced hotel in Paris.

Loved it stay , very good location and hairs salon round the corner. Perfect spot for shopping near to Hermes and LV . Staff it’s very polite and helpful . If you looking for short break in Paris that’s the right place.

Really enjoyed our stay. Friendly and helpful staff. Perfect location. Loved the family room. Only feedback we have is the survey that wasn't read by the reception staff. So the champagne (surprise for the rest of the family) wasn't in the room. But the rest more than compensated.

Very comfortable beds and great shower and location was perfect. However, room was for 4 adults and very, very small. Not a lot in kitchen area - not even a bottle opener. But for a 2 day break it was perfect for us

Don’t ever ever ever ever ever make the mistake to stay in this hotel. I found a dead rat in the wardrobe when I opened it to put my clothes inside. I obviously then decided that I don’t want to stay in that room, as common knowledge rats have diseases. Imagine what else is crawling in this authentic central Parisian dump. The receptionist told me that they will charge me cancellation fee and all the days I had booked if I would leave. His suggestion was for him to throw the rats corps and that he would provide me free breakfast in the morning!!! (Zero hygene ) They said that they will never return my money back and that Paris is full of rats and that it was normal. Hopefully this shameful place will be erased at some point from the hospitality map because they clearly are a gang of amateurs.

Stayed at this hotel in November, the room was so small and nothing like we expected but we made do. We didn’t get any wi-if for the three days we was there even though I let the concierge know many of times. I paid £270 deposit on arrival in case of damage’s. When leaving they told me I will receive my money back within 4 hours … I’m still waiting 4 WEEKS LATER!! contacted them over 20 times and they just say “we sent it” but they clearly are lying! Wouldn’t say again!

Very small rooms, there are no services such as not providing drinking water in the rooms on a daily basis and there are no additional keys upon request because I need it because I have children with me in addition to the rooms need a card to run the electricity

Hotel is very well located near the Champs-Élysées. They could really upgrade the lighting, especially in the kitchenette area. The hotel supplied enough fresh towels for our family of four which was appreciated. Otherwise everything was great.

I stayed there for the second time and enjoyed it again very much. The location is perfect vor visiting the inner-city. Eiffel Tower, Arc de Triomphe, Louvre - everything is within walking distance. :-)

stayed in suite Phillipe Le Bel --- location is very good, staff was perfect --- apartment was not acceptable. Kitchen area much too dark to use, too few cooking utensils annd supplies.. Microwave in back of cupboard under sink. Stove is induction burners with no instructons. Very bright but no ventilation as windows dont open. No where for suitcases No where for clothes storage - no shelves or dresser. Hanging cupboard is very small with three hangers. Bed is too big for room -- only access is to climb on bed. TV on wall beside bed - impossible to watch, Staircase to bed is very difficult for anyone with climbing problems. No bedside table or shelves for books,, glasses, etc.

Very central place with really friendly and helpful team. Clean and nice rooms, absolutely quiet, a place to rest after the day, before starting the night Overall excellent, only the external corners of the shower place need a review.

wonderful and beautiful hotel
Suite equipped with kitchenette and microwave refrigerator,
the bathroom with Nux products
well located in the center of the Champs-Elysées a few minutes from the Eiffel Tower
I thank the entire reception team for their warm welcome

Not only are the rooms small, they are not very clean. The building is old with little insulation; many things do not work right, if at all, and you can hear your next door neighbors. This place made me sad, and I ended up changing hotels just to not let it ruin my trip.

EVERYTHING is broken or missing, and you cannot use VPN on the internet. They’re completely unwilling to fix the problem. I would NEVER stay here again, or recommend this place to my worst enemy. The staff want to argue and not fix the problem, or provide great customer service. If you want a better place to stay, try Motel 6. If you are not on the top floor, be prepared to hear stomping all night long.

This hotel is in a good location and pretty clean. The entire staff is friendly and very accommodating. The hotel itself is
The only downside for me was the parking garage that is allotted to hotel guests (it’s only about 3 minutes walking so not far distance unless you forget something important) but to be fair I have a full sized nine seater so getting it down to the sub basement was the only inconvenience but street parking was available so it worked out better to just park in the street.

We enjoyed 2 nights at Helzear Etoile, the room was spacious, quiet and well equiped, staff was very nice and helpful all along the stay and we enjoyed free Biotherm cosmetics samples. Perfect location, convenient private car parking 2 min away, I am used to travel a lot on business and can assure you will get great experience either on business or personal travel at Helzear Boutique hotel & Suites appartments!

We stay only 1 night but is absolutely a superb location if you want to stay in the best area off Paris. Nice staff, nice room and also a good mini bar and Espresso Machine.
I stay there with a friend. Separate bedroom and a good sofa bed in the living room. French balcony.

10 of us stopped here for my friend’s hen do. It was a perfect location and the rooms were clean and tidy. All the staff were helpful but particularly Wills and Ines who went out of their way to help us. Would definitely stop again.

I visit Paris few times a year. My 4 nights stay in this hotel was an excellent experience.The staff is just amazing and very friendly. Special thanks to Ines who welcomes you very warmly. I didn't memorize everyone's name but they were very professional and nice. The location is perfect,all interesting spot are within walk distance, the stores open late at night and on sundays, which is a real advantage. I had only one little issue in my room, the wifi didn't work up there. I definitely recommend this hotel and will go back for sure.

I stayed 2 nights in this hotel. Thanks to the friendly staff, I enjoyed the location on the Champs Elysees, so it was good to walk around and it was nice to have a late-night monoprix.
Especially thanks to Ines.😀
!!!!!!!
괜찮았어요. 근데 후라이팬은 없어요. 글고 캐리어끌고는 은근 샹젤리제거리에서 멀어요
우버를 탑시다
샴푸린스 다 있어요

I stayed at this hotel while visiting paris for 4 nights and upon arrival the staff members insisted we pay a 200€ deposit fully refundable when checking out. When it came to check out i spoke to the staff member and asked how long it would take for this to be refunded to me (as it’s a lot of money and needed it for the rest of my trip) he assured me it would be 3 days maximum. It has now been over a week and still no money. I have been in contact with ines who works at this hotel, she told me the money was never taken from my account (although i had already provided her with evidence that it had) and that i would not be receiving the money back from them!!!! I would not recommend this hotel to anyone. I have been in contact with my bank to get to the bottom of this and will take even further action if this isn’t solved promptly.

This property was disappointing on Many levels. It is not a cheap property , but you basically have one person at reception. So only one person can request something or check-in at a time. Very frustrating! Especially with kids and a long journey and you are made to wait - even if you had dropped your bags off hours before. Then from 7 months before my booking I wanted a quiet room. I booked it. But they moved me . The hotel is NOT noise insulated. You can hear the street on the one side and the school on the other. Without ear plugs I would not have slept. They seem to have just enough “things” to get by each day, for example- their pillows are very flat and we needed two more- they could only find one in the whole hotel. They only have just enough room keys and we had to reprogram the keys a few times. I would not go back and I would not recommend this hotel. When asked for a recommendation for breakfast and a good croissant Inez sent us to fast food place down the road- didn’t even bother going in. On the plus the location is great , but maybe would have preferred the Latin quarter more . Wills was very sweet but could only do so much and when I voiced all my concerns he told the manager who said he can only see me at 1pm- ugh- on my holiday I must mission back to the hotel for a manager I never met once - he was nowhere to be seen. So I left very unhappy. They wanted to move me to another room but that would have meant packing up everything and I had already spent a whole day and night there.

This hotel is in a great location. Very close to Champs Élysées, easy walking distance to the Arc de Triomphe and the Louis V train station. The hotel itself was a little quirky. During our 3-day stay, I never really saw more than one hotel employee in the building at a time. There was a person stationed at a desk to check us in, bring us to our room, check us out, but never saw so much as one other person during our stay. The elevator was very small. When the hotel attendant checked us in and brought us to the elevator to go up to our room, he ran up the stairs and met the elevator on the 3rd floor because he couldn’t fit in the elevator with us and our luggage. The halls were dark and the lights were activated by motion sensors. So when you stepped off the evaluator, the lites came on. The room was for 4 people; 2 adults and 2 teenagers and it was VERY tight on space. In the room that housed the bed for the adults there was about 10” of space on one side of the bed to allow you to approach and get in bed, otherwise, the room was completely filled by the bed. No other furniture or a luggage valet fit in the room. The whole set up was kind of awkward to maneuver with everyone’s luggage, etc. The air conditioning in the room was ok, but kept turning off once the room reached the set temp and then required us to actively turn it back on as the temp rise again, so at one point I woke during the night to find that it was over 80F in the room because the AC had turned off by itself. Happened every night. The 2 teens slept on a pull out couch that seemed to work ok for them, it again, made that room very crowded.
This might be a very nice room/suite for a couple to stay in, but way too small for 4 people. Just couldn’t get out of each other’s way.

I stayed at this hotel for two nights and before they check you in you must pay a 200€ deposit for the room. After checking out I was promised the money will be returned to my account right away or within the 1 hr. It’s been 3 weeks now trying to contact and email the hotel to ask for the return which they say has already been returned to my account which isn’t the case. This hotel is so unhelpful and would suggest not staying here and dealing with this sort of stuff when on holidays. I have begun to speak with my lawyer and bank. Lets hope for the best

It was such a pleasant experience staying with you guys. You have an amazing location. And with the immaculate linens and last but not the least, great hospitality, specially by Mills and Khalil, you made our stay truly memorable!!

Cheers!!

Clean rooms and great staff. The location of the hotel was perfect, few minutes walk to the Champs- Elysées. The room was very clean and the bed was comfortable. The staff, especially Ines was so kind and helpful. She helped us to find a taxi to the airport on a Saturday morning when the Yellow vests protest was going. She spoke very clear Arabic. She helped us with the luggage as well. Thank you so much Ines.

This hotel is super clean and in an excellent location. The hotel staff were very helpful.
We booked a one bedroom apart hotel due to snoring issues. The room ceiling was very high so this allowed a sub floor to be built as a bedroom. Although very small the room was really clean and the shower room very functional with towels and toiletries. Chambermaid folded my daughter comfortere which was so sweet.
HOWEVER the "bedroom" was not good for us but WAS nice. It had a glass wall and no door., The stairs to the room were very narrow and steep. The softbed was comfortable and the air con excellent =They also had black out curtains HURRAH. The lack of a proper bedroom was an issue for us as we need me the snorer to no disturb my daughters. BUT if that is not an issue for you then I would 100% recommend it. There is a school behind the hotel so at 8.45 children and school bell can be heard

Thanks for all friendly staff Waseem , Mariam , Sabrina and all
Room was very clean and well furnished
Hotel has perfect location with easy walk to champs elysee , with reasonable rates
I used to come to this hotel several times

My son-in-law booked two suites for us all, for our new year break in Paris. The situation could not have been better, as it was within walking distance of the Arc de Triomphe and the Eiffel Tower. The suites were kept spotlessly clean and the reception staff were very helpful. We will definitely return in the future, when we plan to visit Paris again.

Ending my 2 weeks stay in Etoile location after spending 10days in Marceau location; I reiterate my previous review. Very well located. Super kind staff. Loved the trendy deco and the books in room. As soon as I said that the entrance perfume bothers me they turned it off!👍🏻

The hotel is close to major shopping areas and within walking distance to metro stations. Rooms are comfortable and wifi speed is fast. Rooms aren't large, but maybe a little larger as compared to many Paris hotels that consider 10 sqm sufficient space for a room. Staff is very helpful and courteous, especially Ines who helped me to organize transport to the railway station during the recent riots in Paris. Overall highly recommended.

This is my third stay at this property since summer 2018..

Excellent location.. clean rooms..

I would recommend this hotel to both individuals and families..

There is a lovely Moroccan restaurant about 4 mins walk from the property.. many many other restaurant options.. but pls make sure to make a reservation in advance..

I really enjoyed my stay in this hotel. The location is perfect. It's close to the Arc de Triomphe and it's about 25 minute walk to the Eiffel Tower. Metro station is within a 5 minute walk so I didn't waste any time getting around in Paris. Our room was clean and nice. Staff was friendly and helpful. I would definitely stay here again.

We stayed here for 2 nights when in Paris before a cruise. The hotel is just a couple of blocks from the Georges V metro stop. This made travel to/from the airport and all Paris sites easy to access. The room was spacious and clean. We would definitely stay there again.

Like an earlier reviewer said, four stars seems a bit of an exaggeration for this hotel. For starters, it’s barely a hotel. It’s serviced apartments and doesn’t have a restaurant, dining room, or bar, though apparently breakfast can be ordered to the room. We had a 3-bedroom apartment, which is not actually one coherent unit but rather two standard rooms and a one-bedroom apartment located together on a separate corridor, though in our case there was another room on that corridor plus the luggage storage room, so a bit of foot traffic. Three separate rooms suited us well as each of the apartments has its own bathroom and kitchenette. Since the hotel is almost brand-new, all the rooms were in very good shape.
The hotel looks stylish but seemed to put style over substance. For example, our standard room was quite tiny and the only places to put suitcases were the foldable table and a chair. We didn’t use the kitchenette except for putting a couple of bottles in the fridge, and the fridge didn’t seem to be cooling at all. The bed was on the soft side though still comfortable, the closet was tiny with only four hangers, and the bathroom had a heated towel rack, which was a nice touch, but the towels weren’t particularly plush. There was no phone in the room, meaning no way to contact another room or reception other than physically walking there. No slippers or body lotion are provided. All the rooms have names rather than numbers, but the key cards go by numbers, so the front desk actually has a list of numbers and corresponding names. The name of the room doesn’t seem to have anything to do with the (tasteful but sparse) decor. Odd.
More negatively, service is not a strength of this hotel. Checking in and out was a slow, confused process with lots of handwritten paperwork and lots of moving around. The front desk staff were generally not very helpful with information and didn’t seem to know much about the area. Their demeanor ranged from friendly to gruff and they certainly did not make you feel welcome as you walked in. It is also quite odd that they have to open the front door for each arriving guest, and if no one is at the desk, you wait, with no way to call anybody. Housekeeping one day forgot a large trash bag in our room, which really shouldn’t happen. For a four-star hotel, I’d expect more consistency and helpfulness in service.
The location of the hotel is good, very close to the Champs Elysées with lots of high-end shopping and within a five-minute walk of a metro station and about 10 minutes to the Arc de Triomphe. There are plenty of restaurants around, as well as a couple of breakfast place. However, being rich and upscale, the area is not very interesting and the restaurants are all quite expensive, so the Marais or Bastille area might be a better option for local flavor.
The price was very good for Paris at about 135 Euro per room per night but that may have been because we stayed in late September and booked far in advance. Would we stay here again? Not likely. The lack of service and amenities plus some of the hotel’s odd features made staying there less pleasant and easy than it should be.

Perfect location with the price .
professional staff.
It amazing stay in hotel good safety on door and room.
Nice greetings when I arrived .
Very good cleanliness.

But air conditioning is not much to cool.

This hotel is unique because of its staff. I have never seen a welcoming staff like them, specially Inas
The quality manager kept sending me to make sure that my staying is comfortable.
The family was super happy, it is very clean too

we were a group of 5 adults. we booked a 3 bedroom appartment. the hotel is practically brand new clean and well equiped. in each room we had a microwave, cooker, kettle, small refrigerator, glasses, mugs, dishes, forks, knives, spoons, pan, casserole, toiletries, towels (changed daily).
the staff is very respectful and always ready to help.
it had a charming terrasse that made us feel like we were home, were we could sit and have a coffe or a drink
it is close to Georges 5 station (3mn walk) and Charles Degaulle - etoile metro station (4mn) from wich u can reach all parts of Paris. there is a drugstore nearby and a mini market called G20. also nearby we can find a "pret a manger" and a bakery. the champs elysees is 3 minutes away and there u can find all sorts of restaurants and cafes and also a "brioche doree" bakery. L'arc de triomphe is 4 mn away and the eiffel tower is 15 minutes walk.
we enjoyed our stay and would love to visit it again.

My experience with this hotel has been terrible. It looks like a great place online but we didn't stay here so I don't know if it's great or not. What I do know is they charge your credit card without authorization. I booked in April 2018 and cancelled for free the next day - I have the email confirming that it was cancelled for free, without charge. In July 2018 they suddenly charged my credit card! I've been calling and emailing them for a month now, they keep promising to put through a refund on my credit card but they never do. I've called/emailed them at least 6 times, always waiting a few days between calls because they promise accounting is reversing the charges that very day. I check my credit card every few days and of course, no refund. I've spent alot of time dealing with this, and paid to call France long distance. I had to pay the charge already ($1658 CDN) on my credit card so I wouldn't incur interest. I'm hoping this is cleared up soon. Perhaps a lovely place to stay, but not a lovely place to deal with when they've obviously made an error!

My friend and I travelled to Paris and selected this beautiful hotel. This is situated close to trams, Arc de Triomphe, and Champes-Elysees. It is fairly easy to navigate your way around Paris. We loved our little room which came with a coffee machine, sink, hob, and all utensils you could possibly need. The receptionists and staff are very friendly and lovely. We arrived before our check in time but were allowed to check in slightly earlier which was a plus. It also has a lovely little terrace area which is very pretty and the view of the gardens were beautiful from our room. The only little incident we had was when I got stuck in the bathroom, they are sliding doors and it had become jammed. My friend dashed downstairs to Wills (Who checked us in) who came rushing to my aid and broke me free of the rather funny event. Wills was amazing and made us both feel very welcome, we also had a running joke about me being the singer Adele (I'm obviously not) but he would sing her songs to us. A very amazing and friendly guy who kept us smiling throughout our short stay in this beautiful city. Would definitely recommend, just don't close the bathroom door!! I would love to come back to this hotel in the future when I plan my next trip here.

We stayed at the Hotel Helzear Etoile for five nights. We had initially booked a two bedroom suite for five people but there had been a problem with the suite. We were put into other adjoining rooms which we were more than satisfied with. Christopher greeted us on reception and was extremely friendly and very helpful as were all the other members of reception.
The rooms were very clean and smart and the cleaning staff thorough and polite.
There was a tranquil outdoor seating area where you could sit and relax with a drink and a book.
The hotel is a two minute walk two the Arc de Triomphe and the Champs Elysees. We found that George V Metro Station was the most convenient. Nice ‘Pret a Manger’ just around the corner too.
I would not hesitate to recommend this lovely hotel!

Quality apartment with excellent location.Staffs were nice and helpful.
It was my fabulous trip in Paris with family
The apt just 2 mins walk from Georgev metro..also easy to go to sightseeing place such as Eiffle tower, Bateau Mouch,Louvre Museum.

We stay 1 night in this beautiful hotel (3 adults and 1 baby) the room was big, very clean and comfortable, the staff were so helpful and kind.
The location is perfect!! minutes walking from l’arc de triomphe, and the Eiffel Tower! I highly recommend!

We booked a room from April 12th-15th. The hotel wasn't supposed to charge until the day we checked out. However, they charged our credit card for over $1600 on April 11th, the day before we got there. We weren't aware of this since we were traveling and paid $1,058.63 when we checked out. We requested Expedia to have the hotel refund our money when we found the extra charge. The hotel refused to refund and responded the charge was for extra consumption which they miraculously knew even we weren't there yet when they charged it. As of today, they still haven't refunded our money and keep making excuses. Don't stay here, they will steal your money when they have your credit card number. We were lucky they charged before we were there. It would be impossible to prove if they charged us the day after...Yet they're still keeping our money!!!
Please stay away from this place. The owner and manager here are scammers. One of us is a travel agent and we were traveling around checking out hotels and places.

Our family of 4 had a very comfortable stay at this property.

The one bedroom deluxe suite is similar to a loft bedroom..

Amazing location.. a 5 minute walk from champs Elysee..

I would highly recommend the hotel to individual as well as families visiting Paris..

We stayed at this property for two nights and it was perfect for my wife and our two boys 10 and 13. The kids slept on a pull out and were very comfortable. My wife and I slept in the next room and had lots of room for our bags. The small kitchenette was useful and a nice espresso maker in the room was a nice touch. Air conditioning was great making our stay very comfortable. Great location, just a short walk to the Champs Elysse and the Arch de Triumphe.

We booked 2 suites, one family of 4 and one family of 5. Our bookings were for the Champs Elysee branch on Avenue Maceau, but when we arrived one of the bookings was put into the Etoile branch - so we the manager Soleil arranged for moving us all to the Etoile branch.
Upon entrance - it was light and airy. The hotel is "simple", but all the essentials are there. For example, a coffee machine, kettle, sink, kitchenette. The amenity kit could be further improved - but had soap, shampoo and conditioner.
The price we paid would be a "luxury" price in other cities - but in Paris - we struggled to find "family accommodation for 5". This "Suite" option was the cheapest we could find in a good location. But in other cities - this would have been a luxury price tag €450 - €500 per night.

Location: Excellent (it is essentially behind the Champs Elysee)
Price: Expensive
Room size: Very good for Paris
Amenities: the essentials were there (bring your own slippers and shower cap)
Service: Excellent

The 5 stars are for the service we received. Though there were a few hiccups with bookings and housekeeping, the management team worked tirelessly to put things right for us. This goes for saying it was from the housekeeping team to senior management - everyone was friendly and everyone was helpful.You will not be disappointed because the staff work very hard to make things right and going above and beyond.

I definitely recommend the hotel for large families who want to be at a good location.

A big "thank you" to the team to making our stay right! With a special thank you to Soleil and Assane.

We were in an emergency situation...when our original accommodation fell through....at 7.30pm a family of four we home less...Helzear saved us....and while the space was small by Australian standards.... quality of accommodation and service was very high....The location was fantastic for a family happy to walk everywhere....we walked to Eiffel Tower, Champs Elysee and Arc Triomphe. Away from the tourist areas we found reasonable priced restaurants for families...we loved it and will recommend it...

We booked the hotel with confirmation email showing the hotel address, however when we arrived, staff said we need to go to another wing of the hotel across the road.

Room is nice, clean and tidy.

Staff are friendly and helpful.

Location is ok, 8 minutes walk to metro station.

No slippers, toothbrush and shower cap. We had to request towels and shower gel replenishment.

We were asked to pay tax when checking out the hotel even our booking was pre paid online. No sure if it’s the practice of Paris hotels, we paid €27 anyway for a 3 nights stay, as we were rushing to leave and had no time to investigate.

The front desk staff is very helpful. We did get accommodated with the connecting duplex for our family visit. We were a family of five and required additional toiletries, the front desk staff came through. The room was always done even when we left late in the day for our daily excursions. Close to shopping & various restaurants. As any City, it does get a little noisy at street level, but AC, room and bedding were very comfortable.

This would have been a 5 star review- the staff were super friendly and accommodating, the 1 bedroom suite I originally had was very comfortable, location was excellent. The reasons why I could not give it5 stars was the elevator broke down on Saturday and did not get fixed until Tuesday. It was very difficult going up and down the stairs- they tried to do what they could but could not really fix the problem- they did transfer me to the ground floor on Tuesday. Consistency in their message needs to be improved- different people tended to give different information- from the aurport transfer at arrival to the elevator and room problem. But again, they were very friendly and wanting to please so I probably will go back but requedt a ground floor room😀

This is a lovely hotel in an excellent location. My daughter and I were well taken care of by the friendly staff. They spoke English. Clean and quiet. On a pretty street very very close to the Champs Elysee and the Arc de Triumphe. Very safe. Highly recommend

I was going to stay at this hotel on a business trip. The hotel canceled my reservation in the afternoon of the arrival day due to overbooking. But they still charged fully charged my credit card and never made a refund. I have now been waiting for 7 weeks and still have not received the refund whenever I am contacting them the responsible person is either not yet there or on vacation.

We traveled with young children. We booked a duplex apartment with 3 bedrooms but was given 3 singles rooms. The staff just replied that duplex was no available (although our booking was accepted).

The next day, at the reception, we overheard a quarrel at reception table over another family who booked duplex but was given separate single rooms. Staff replied ‘it’s the first time we have people like you complaining’.

I am speechless with the way they handle customer bookings and room allocations.

NO STAR if fill possible
Booked 3 bedrooms apartment for summer directly from hotel website. Got confirmation and everything. 2 weeks ago received email from hotel saying something due to ad-work, our reservation got cancel. Panic I start search for another place to stay on booking.com. Exactly same day the 3 bedrooms is available BUT with DOUBLE of the PRICE. So this hotel is lying! This is ridiculous and unacceptable how they doing business.
STAY AWAY with this hotel! Not worth to ruining your vacay with last minute cancellation because of these ripoff people.

I stayed at the hotel with my partner for the weekend. We were lucky to have a cooperating weather. We felt at ease as soon as we walked into the hotel, it was welcoming. The members of staff were very qualified and made sure that everything was going smoothly. The location of the hotel is also very convenient, we were near all the main attractions such as the Champs Elysees - we were able to shop, eat and enjoy the sun all from one area. The best part of the stay was probably the view from the balcony, I really enjoyed waking up to that. The only thing I would say though is I wish the check-in was quicker, although they were welcoming, I was tired and wish I could have been in my room faster. I would recommend and will be going back :).

Liked the location but other than that it’s an average hotel. Lack of towels and no tissue at all in room. No free bottles of water. Staff didn’t welcome us when we first arrived, it was like we were invisible, no one talked to us or said anything

We had a one night stay in the Junior Suite on the 1st floor. The apartment was everything I hoped. It was really delightful and exactly what I imagine Paris city living to be. It was about 5min walk to Champs Elysees... closer to the Arc de Triomphe end. We were going to the Lido show and it was a very easy walk. Being so closer send to CE you have more restaurant, public transport, taxi, pharmacy, cinema, luxury goods stores etc. Very close to Blvgari and Louis Vuitton so be careful!! The room was dressed with beautiful Alessi housewares, the kitchenette was a perfect size. I loved that an apartment also had mini bar! Shower was a great size and bathroom is modern although I think the tap is wrong for the sink as water spills on the benches be careful. Huge window in living area which overlooked the street. Beautiful flooring and gorgeous timber staircase leading to a lift bedroom with window partitions. We had a late check out for 12 which was fantastic plus kept our bags in storage after check out for a few hours while we explored the area. I don't know whether the cost compared with other places close by but considering the location, the room, service and everything else, I felt I got value for money at 149€ for Saturday night.

We stayed here for two nights on family trip. Beautiful nicely done new hotel in great part of Paris. Great location, many parking places for car ( for additional cost ).

Beds are very comfortable, bathrooms clean with luxury products. Room has got minibar and coffee machine.

Close to major sites of Paris. Loads good food outlets around. Supermarket 5 min walk away.

Stayed here for one night and was extremely disappointed. The term 'suites' gives the impression that the room is bigger than the norm but it is exactly the opposite. I actually banged my shoulder on the TV trying to walk past the bed. The hotel is in an excellent position for the Champs-Elysée and is expensive obviously because of that but the only thing provided by the hotel is a bed for the night but due to the noise level sleep is not an option. It is on a very busy road at the front and overlooks a residential area and school at the rear, neither conducive to sleep. Also there are no mirrors in the room, only the bathroom, pretty useless for drying your hair. On the plus side it is spotlessly clean and the female receptionist is extremely helpful.

I stay in this hotel for six days, great location and service was great. I will try it again next time I m in paris. It s perfect for a family trip, The suites was bigger then most places I stayed before.

Wonderful stay very near , less than 3 minutes to be in Champs Élysée
New. Hotel very elegant and different great rate for all the 4 stars and staff want to help
I will recommend this hotel great adress ,very clean and quiet excellent wifi .
when we arrive nobody tell us about the Tera are
But in the next day ,we met Ines at the front desk and she present the hotel like she is the owner . And she invite us to visit the terrasse and it was my wife's birthday
We spent a great moment ..don't hesitate to ask about the terrasse you can even smoke inside ..ines presented also for us the helzear group and yes we will visit the helzear Montparnasse ,to enjoy the appartement with sauna and jacousie

Hotel is announcing its’ suites as a “bedroom, living room and dining area” for a promotional ~250 euros a night. In fact, it is a small siting/kitchen area downstairs and a VERY narrow stairs to the second level, where the bed is. Kitchen area does not have any light. There are no phones in the room to call reception! We unpacked only to discover that our room did not have hot water (!). After some discussion that we really want to have hot water, we were transferred to another room on the ground floor, small studio type, room being just a little bigger than the bed. If you are there, you will hear every sound from the street and from your neighbors, but at least you will be on one level and with hot water. We asked our room to be cleaned at noon, however it still was not at 5pm, and the very service oriented reception person told us that they start cleaning from the top third floor and have not yet reached the ground one. No more comments.

We had a great stay. Very comfortable and clean, with quality fixtures and fittings. As it is newly refurbished, there are still some issues that need resolving, such as the fridge not working. As we were on a road trip across Europe, all the food we transferred from our car cool box to the fridge went off. I think maybe the fridge turns off when you exit the room and all the electricity, lights, etc go off. Other than that, the hotel was great and if the issues can be resolved, I wouldn't hesitate to recommend this hotel / Aparthotel to others.

I had a wonderful time at this Parisian style boutique hotel that has just opened. The decoration is beautiful and the staff very helpful. The hotel is very well located and I highly recommend to stay there if you want to live like a Parisian.

I stayed for a night at Helzear's new hotel rue Christophe Colomb in Paris 8th, what a terrible idea I had. At first I was welcomed by a very nice woman who welcomed me very gently. I quickly realized however that the hotel was absolutely not ready to be opened. The paint smell was horrendous and workers were finishing a little bit everything everywhere.
I was told that because they had not received their computers, I had to do my checkin in their other hotel (49 avenue Marceau)...
When I got there, the man at the reception was far less welcoming. I managed to check in and went back to my initial hotel.
The room was neat (it is brand new), small but with all the comfort you can expect: large bed, small kitchen, but very tiny shower.
I went to work but when I came back it became a nightmare. It was 35 celcius in Paris and they had a power shortage in the hotel. The elevator was broken, so as the Air Conditioning... The communal areas were disgusting (pictures below), i waited but finally I negotiated to have a room in their other hotel just to have an air conditioned room.
There, the room was very very very tiny. The bed was stuck between two walls and you could only access it from the front (never saw something like that).
The receptionist at 12 rue Christophe Colomb was very nice but that will be my only positive aspect I will take home. Avoid at all cost until it is ready to open properly, and be careful of the price that can seem attractive because the rooms are really really small.
